&gt;&gt; Because there are external sources of lactase,

00:07:11.380 --> 00:07:14.620
why does it have, why, what was the advantage

00:07:14.620 --> 00:07:17.840
of producing it internally to the human organism? And

00:07:17.840 --> 00:07:19.860
that's the question that I focused on early on

00:07:19.860 --> 00:07:22.960
because I thought that was just so very fascinating.

00:07:22.960 --> 00:07:25.180
On top of the food value, on top of

00:07:25.180 --> 00:07:27.390
whatever you can get from yogurt and kefir and

00:07:27.390 --> 00:07:32.800
cheese and sour milk. Wh-, what, what's the advantage

00:07:32.800 --> 00:07:35.910
of drinking fresh milk as an adult? Especially when

00:07:35.910 --> 00:07:40.210
so many societies must have regarded it as repugnant,

00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:41.860
because it would cause diarrhea.

00:07:41.860 --> 00:07:42.140
&gt;&gt; Sure.

00:07:42.140 --> 00:07:47.260
&gt;&gt; To humans, it was. You're intolerant. And

00:07:47.260 --> 00:07:49.030
you know, the debate is still running. But

00:07:49.030 --> 00:07:51.800
the theory, the leading theory that I like,

00:07:51.800 --> 00:07:54.640
is the, and that the data seems to support,

