[LAUGH]

00:26:18.471 --> 00:26:21.150
&gt;&gt; Big bags of a laxative brought to you

00:26:21.150 --> 00:26:23.680
by the friendly people of the United States of America.

00:26:23.680 --> 00:26:24.680
&gt;&gt;

00:26:23.680 --> 00:26:24.840
[LAUGH]

00:26:24.840 --> 00:26:26.740
And this came to my attention before I

00:26:26.740 --> 00:26:29.440
even heard of the phenomenon of lactose intolerance. I

00:26:29.440 --> 00:26:32.020
was touring. I, I did some field in rural

00:26:32.020 --> 00:26:35.880
El Salvador. I was working a tiny community called

00:26:35.880 --> 00:26:36.090
[FOREIGN].

00:26:36.090 --> 00:26:39.290
The mayor was taking me around town. Showing me

00:26:39.290 --> 00:26:42.320
this is our grainary. This is our well. He took

00:26:42.320 --> 00:26:45.690
me to the school house. And we walked in

00:26:45.690 --> 00:26:47.810
and met the children. The teacher turned them out so

00:26:47.810 --> 00:26:49.520
they could come out and sing a song for

00:26:49.520 --> 00:26:51.840
me, or whatever. And then walked through the school, looking

00:26:51.840 --> 00:26:56.570
at the very simple infrastructure of the school. And in

00:26:56.570 --> 00:27:02.090
the corner were all these bags of donated US dried

00:27:02.090 --> 00:27:05.525
skim milk. And I said

00:27:05.525 --> 00:27:05.590
[FOREIGN]

00:27:05.590 --> 00:27:07.650
why, why are the bags in the school?

00:27:07.650 --> 00:27:09.852
Why aren't people using? Oh, don't worry he said

00:27:09.852 --> 00:27:10.832
[FOREIGN]

00:27:10.832 --> 00:27:15.080
don't worry, we do use the powder in those bags.

00:27:15.080 --> 00:27:17.720
At least twice a year we get the comunity together.

00:27:17.720 --> 00:27:21.450
People bring buckets. We'd put the bags. the powder in

00:27:21.450 --> 00:27:24.030
the bags and water together when we whitewashed the schoolhouse.

00:27:24.030 --> 00:27:25.030
&gt;&gt;

00:27:24.030 --> 00:27:24.649
[LAUGH]

00:27:24.649 --> 00:27:26.733
&gt;&gt; We were very grateful for the ability

00:27:26.733 --> 00:27:27.168
[LAUGH]

00:27:27.168 --> 00:27:30.600
to whitewash the school house. And I said but why, why, why, do you use it

00:27:30.600 --> 00:27:35.660
as whitewash? He said, because the people here get sick if they eat that as a,

00:27:35.660 --> 00:27:39.670
the intended food product. And you just imagine,

00:27:39.670 --> 00:27:41.910
then, in the ethnographic literature, there's stories of

00:27:41.910 --> 00:27:44.820
people in Bali, lining up to receive small

00:27:44.820 --> 00:27:48.554
vials to put it in their family apothecary.

00:27:48.554 --> 00:27:49.186
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:27:49.186 --> 00:27:52.336
&gt;&gt; Family drug supply. If they ever need

00:27:52.336 --> 00:27:58.180
a laxative, they can take U.S. food aid. But we sent thousands of

00:27:58.180 --> 00:28:04.550
pounds a year of dried, powdered skim milk to a population where 80% are

00:28:04.550 --> 00:28:08.350
lactose malabsorbers. As a general human population.

00:28:09.600 --> 00:28:11.350
I think that's one of the least

00:28:11.350 --> 00:28:15.020
exposed and, and most obvious gaffes, of

00:28:15.020 --> 00:28:18.610
assuming that what's true in our society.

00:28:18.610 --> 00:28:21.060
We have a high frequency of lactose malabsorbers

00:28:21.060 --> 00:28:23.650
because of the Northern European population that was

00:28:23.650 --> 00:28:26.760
important in the founding and, and the relative

00:28:26.760 --> 00:28:28.790
growth rate compared to the Native Americans of

00:28:28.790 --> 00:28:28.860
[LAUGH]

00:28:28.860 --> 00:28:30.970
the United States, so we have a high,

00:28:30.970 --> 00:28:34.670
relatively high frequency of lactase persistence. In adulthood.

00:28:34.670 --> 00:28:35.595
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:28:35.595 --> 00:28:38.070
&gt;&gt; And we assumed, oh just look at

00:28:38.070 --> 00:28:41.030
the billboards and things we had. Everybody needs milk.

00:28:41.030 --> 00:28:41.823
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:28:41.823 --> 00:28:43.770
&gt;&gt; You never outgrow your need for milk.

00:28:43.770 --> 00:28:46.370
Or remember that curve, you exactly do outgrow

00:28:46.370 --> 00:28:49.250
your need for milk. And most adults do.

00:28:49.250 --> 00:28:52.850
But yet, we had this cultural, let us say,

00:28:54.080 --> 00:28:56.800
a cultural cocoon that said oh, people,

00:28:56.800 --> 00:28:59.080
everybody needs milk. You never outgrow your need

00:28:59.080 --> 00:29:04.400
for milk. Milk does a body good. We had all these messages, and so we started

00:29:04.400 --> 00:29:07.670
shipping milk powder, thinking it was easy

00:29:07.670 --> 00:29:10.430
to concentrate, Right? You can take milk and

00:29:10.430 --> 00:29:12.310
make it dried skim milk. You could ship

00:29:12.310 --> 00:29:16.925
it quickly. It stores well. The schoolhouse in

00:29:16.925 --> 00:29:17.150
[FOREIGN]

00:29:17.150 --> 00:29:19.175
I'm sure still has some in the corner

00:29:19.175 --> 00:29:21.070
[LAUGH]

00:29:21.070 --> 00:29:23.050
and people found lots of different ways to use it.

00:29:23.050 --> 00:29:24.050
&gt;&gt; Wow.

00:29:24.050 --> 00:29:24.780
&gt;&gt; Amazing.

00:29:24.780 --> 00:29:26.160
&gt;&gt; That is an amazing story.

00:29:26.160 --> 00:29:29.280
&gt;&gt; It is. And so what that helps you to realize is that.

00:29:30.720 --> 00:29:32.950
it's important, I think especially important

00:29:32.950 --> 00:29:34.300
for North Americans to open their eyes

00:29:34.300 --> 00:29:40.580
and realize that what our genes encourage by way of cultural activities and,

00:29:40.580 --> 00:29:44.860
and cultural environment is not necessarily the same for the rest of the world.

00:29:44.860 --> 00:29:47.420
&gt;&gt; That's exactly right.

00:29:49.530 --> 00:29:53.340
That's really all the questions I have. Is there anything else you would ask?

00:29:53.340 --> 00:29:56.490
&gt;&gt; It's a classic example, you know. It's such a wonderful example of

00:29:56.490 --> 00:30:01.260
the interplay of, of genes and of culture. we often use it for that.

00:30:01.260 --> 00:30:01.753
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm

00:30:01.753 --> 00:30:04.419
&gt;&gt; And model genes and cultures, two parallel tracks

00:30:04.419 --> 00:30:08.658
and semi-independent tracks of inheritance. And what's so great is

00:30:08.658 --> 00:30:10.530
in this particular case you can see how well

00:30:10.530 --> 00:30:14.470
there's an environmental challenge coming through in lysine and calcium.

00:30:14.470 --> 00:30:17.880
And you can see how you could change your culture and adopt

00:30:17.880 --> 00:30:21.580
the drinking of pinniped livers and solve the problem. We can see how

00:30:21.580 --> 00:30:25.110
you can evolve a high frequency of the big L gene and

00:30:25.110 --> 00:30:29.130
solve the problem. Or you can live someplace, where that problem is less.

00:30:29.130 --> 00:30:30.091
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:30:30.091 --> 00:30:31.350
&gt;&gt; And and the problem is

00:30:31.350 --> 00:30:35.340
actually, maybe protecting yourself against sunlight and,

00:30:35.340 --> 00:30:39.470
and ultraviolet, and so therefore the high melanization. What I love is this,

00:30:39.470 --> 00:30:42.080
this idea that, to understand the human organism,

00:30:42.080 --> 00:30:46.800
you can't just study the genes. Or the culture,

00:30:46.800 --> 00:30:51.540
you have to have 'em both on the table. And you have to think about both of

00:30:51.540 --> 00:30:54.360
them. How they interact, how they may compensate

00:30:54.360 --> 00:30:56.990
for one another, how they may influence one another.

00:30:56.990 --> 00:31:00.486
Because a totally successful adaptation on the part of

00:31:00.486 --> 00:31:05.240
demelanization would have. If it had been completely successful,

00:31:05.240 --> 00:31:09.670
you would be not very likely to see the evolution of lactase persistence.

00:31:09.670 --> 00:31:09.725
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:31:09.725 --> 00:31:13.490
&gt;&gt; But it solved the problem. And what it shows you is that it helped. But

00:31:13.490 --> 00:31:14.580
that, that there was, there is still a

00:31:14.580 --> 00:31:17.750
recurring calcium deficiency at high latitude. Which we

00:31:17.750 --> 00:31:23.060
know from records and, other things. So I just love this idea that the, the, the

00:31:23.060 --> 00:31:26.240
study of the human organism involves thinking about

00:31:26.240 --> 00:31:28.920
different kinds of inheritance and their interaction in time.

00:31:28.920 --> 00:31:30.610
&gt;&gt; Thank

00:31:30.610 --> 00:31:31.180
you so much.

00:31:31.180 --> 00:31:32.070
&gt;&gt; Of course. Thank you.

